      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to clinical performance indicators for pedicle screw construct integrity.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to load sharing and adjacent-segment effects; yield force is a direct surrogate for implant fatigue life initiation; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield energy absorption. All three QoIs are required outputs in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant submissions. Relevance to COU is high."
